<!-- ================== EXECUTIVE SUMMARY ================== -->

<div class="page">
    <h2>Executive Summary</h2>

```
<p>This proposal presents a pragmatic digital transformation solution for <strong>Naveen General Store</strong> using a <strong>WhatsApp-first ordering system</strong>. Unlike expensive mobile apps that suffer from low customer adoption, this approach leverages customers’ existing behavior to drive immediate operational efficiency and revenue growth.</p>

<div class="kpi">
    <div class="kpi-box">
        <div class="kpi-value">+100%</div>
        <div>Order Volume</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-box">
        <div class="kpi-value">-90%</div>
        <div>Order Processing Time</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-box">
        <div class="kpi-value">-85%</div>
        <div>Missed Orders</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-box">
        <div class="kpi-value">30–60 Days</div>
        <div>ROI Period</div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="box">
    <strong>Strategic Insight:</strong> Customers already use WhatsApp daily. By digitizing this existing behavior instead of forcing a new app, adoption is immediate, costs are low, and results are measurable from day one.
</div>

<h3>Investment Snapshot</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Component</th><th>Cost</th><th>Timeline</th></tr>
