<!-- ================== MARKET & STRATEGY ================== -->

<div class="page">
    <h2>Market Context & Strategic Positioning</h2>

```
<h3>Industry Reality</h3>
<p>Quick-commerce platforms (Blinkit, Zepto, Swiggy Instamart) compete on speed and discounts. However, they lack the trust, flexibility, and local relationships that define neighborhood stores.</p>

<h3>Core Advantages of Naveen General Store</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Strength</th><th>Business Value</th><th>How Technology Amplifies It</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Personal Relationships</td><td>High customer trust</td><td>Order history and preference tracking</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Credit Facility</td><td>Customer loyalty</td><td>Digital tracking and reminders</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Local Product Knowledge</td><td>Right inventory</td><td>Instant catalog updates</td></tr>
    <tr><td>WhatsApp Usage</td><td>Zero learning curve</td><td>Immediate customer adoption</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Why WhatsApp First</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Approach</th><th>Build Cost</th><th>Monthly Cost</th><th>Adoption</th><th>Time to ROI</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Mobile App</td><td>₹2–3L</td><td>₹15–25k</td><td>10–15%</td><td>6–12 months</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Website</td><td>₹80k–1.2L</td><td>₹5–8k</td><td>20–30%</td><td>3–6 months</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>WhatsApp System</strong></td><td><strong>₹50–60k</strong></td><td><strong>₹2–3k</strong></td><td><strong>80%+</strong></td><td><strong>1–2 months</strong></td></tr>
</table>
```

